caption: Best burrito in town. Most places serve a burrito the size of a Chinese egg roll, but not here, their burrito is huge!  The tacos are grand also. Great hole in the wall restaurant.  They are very generous in their serving.  You will leave this place with a full belly.
Had a excellent experience in here with my kids. The food was served quick and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are reasonable.

So happy I took a chance on this restaurant! First off, great service-- very friendly! More importantly, though, tasty food!!! Lazy dog offers a wide range of foods from noodles to burgers. I ordered fried hush puppies which were more like fried mash potato balls mmm. I tried all the homemade sauces with the starter. All tasted fresh, and I really loved the molasses barbecue. After the hush puppies, I had the original burger with bite + bark sauce. The sauce was like a thousand island sauce with paprika. A perfect combo. Finally, I had the banana pudding. So yummy!!

caption: Please ignore any negative reviews this place rocked!!!  I don’t Evan know where to start with how amazing this place is. The woman on the phone was incredibly sweet and caring she exceeded all expectations, despite a very frustrating error with Uber eats she was understanding and so helpful reassuring me not to worry and just pure genuineness. The food was excellent I am born and raised in sunset park so I am quite familiar with all the good mexican restaurants. But this was beyond good, tacos were fresh and delicious rice and beans well seasoned with a great portion. All the sauces were on point, flavorful distinct and authentic to the T from what you would expect from true Mexican cuisine. The tamale was perfect, the quesadilla was incredibly satisfying and super fresh and tasty. Everything was packed with care and thoughtfulness cold sauces remained cold hot remained hot. Grilled jalapeños and cactus was fantastic included all the fixings limes and radishes a true Gem of sunset I urge everyone with a taste for authentic Mexican food to dine here they Evan sent me dried chili de arbol powder because I mentioned I love spice. I once again want to thank the amazing and caring staff for making this an incredible cinco de Mayo despite the current circumstances  BRAVO!!!!

I know the dish they served me and they were tacos dorados... NOT A QUESADILLA when we asked the waitress why there was no cheese she said we had to ask for the cheese on the quesadilla!!
